people domesticate big cats all over the world, yeah it's dangerous -- look at roy horn -- but it happens. if you feed them, you can train them, just like a normal cat. it's just that the consequences are much worse if they get pissed.

second, you're ignoring that the different survivor groups now that they're maybe 2 years into the outbreak are going to develop differently. herschel's farm had a barn full of zombies. woodbury had a stadium with gladiator fights. but a guy saving and keeping a tiger is too much for you? people would do whatever they wanted to do, once there were no rules other than "survive".
